Mr.
Hall
she
left
to
Caroline
or
rather,
it
was
to
Caroline's
care
Mr.
Hall
consigned
himself.
He
generally
sought
Caroline
in
every
party
where
she
and
he
happened
to
be.
He
was
not
in
general
a
lady's
man,
though
all
ladies
liked
him;
something
of
a
book
worm
he
was,
near
